Real Madrid are preparing to launch an offer of £86million plus winger, James Rodriguez for Chelsea’s midfielder, N’Golo Kante. According to El Desmarque, Real Madrid manager, Zinedine Zidane has identified Kante as a long-time replacement for Luka Modric, who is in the latter stage of his career at Santiago Bernabeu. The Spanish newspaper also reports that Kante dreams of playing for the Los Blancos and has lost faith in the ‘Chelsea project’ under manager, Frank Lampard. Kante has been impressive since joining Chelsea from Leicester City in 2016. The 28-year-old has two Premier League titles, the UEFA Europa League and also the 2018 FIFA World Cup with France. Kante’s Chelsea will take on Newcastle United in the Premier League this weekend. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.